The paper presents a computational model for semantic interpretation of symmetry in naturalistic scenes, which involves methods in computer vision and knowledge representation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) methods. Additionally, the paper evaluates the framework with an empirical study on human perception (cs.HC).
